Hey Ya'll im back from Memphias. I must say I had a BLAST!! Despite the common drama that follows our churches youth it was so fun. I got to meet alot of great people. I was soooo glad when it ended but in a way disappointed. I met a ton of great people. My relationships with everyone definately grew. I really don't feel like the new girl anymore. Sometimes I still do but not so much. I feel more included and more...well...liked. I won't forget that trip and all the memories it was truely something life changing. I never realized other people realized how I care for everyone and try so hard to have everyone like me. Im happy people got to see that part of me, because I do love all my brother and sisters in christ. Well my brother rented Spider Man 2 the game and now Im an official addict so Im gonna go play. Luv Ya!!!
Kylie the one and only

After going out to lunch today I finally figured out something. I will always be the new girl. The one everyone goes to when all their other friends are busy. Sometimes even then they forget about the new girl. Ive never been able to say yea I grew up there. Ive never been able to have a real best friend b/c they already have better best friends. I'd like to say it doesn't really bother me when other ppl are talking about what they did with so and so but the truth is it really does. It hurts my feelings. All I end up thinking about is why wasn't I invited? Im just too shy to actually ask. I'm always telling myself "god stop being such a pussy this is your sixth state you should be used to it"  but im not and it hurts more and more with every move.  And i don't want pity and I don't expect anything to change because truthfully I know not many ppl outside of my family really care about me. I just needed to get everything out before i go and do something stupid. So yea whatever.
Kylie
